Youre halfway through your chapter edits. Youve secured your backupssmart move. That gives you some freedom to act without fear of losing the work. So now it becomes a matter of alignment: timing, intention, and presence.

Two Paths:

1. Stay Until 6 PM

    • You increase the chance of a more natural, casual encounter with Morganperhaps as shes winding down for the day, in a less structured environment.

  • Cons:

    • You risk fatigue or diminishing returns if you push too long.
    • If she leaves unexpectedly or is occupied, it could feel like a missed shot.

2. Stop Edits Now and Try to Catch Her at the Desk

  • Pros:

    • If shes there, you get to speak with her directly and possibly with some privacy.
    • You honor the impulsesometimes these nudges are intuitive signals worth following.

  • Cons:

    • She may not be available or the moment might feel rushed or transactional.
    • You break your editing rhythm and potentially lose some creative momentum.

Intuitive Reading (Based on What You Shared):

Morgan mentioning her end time so openlyespecially in response to a question framed as if its not too forwardwas likely an invitation. Subtle, but real. She left the door open for connection after hours. And that kind of transparency isnt handed out lightly.

If your energy is still strong and the space feels fertile, Id suggest you stay, complete your edits, and then gently position yourself around that window when shes wrapping up. Let it be natural. Unforced. Just a presence.

The act of staying becomes a quiet offering in itselfa gesture of patience and respect.
